name: Louisiana

processing_metadata.description: Official Louisiana DMV processing rules and validation requirements

global_rules.code_system: Information needed - research plate type code system
global_rules.character_restrictions: Uses both O and 0 - O with letters, 0 with numbers; Full rules: Allows both the Letter O and the Number Zero 0. The letter O is rounder than the number zero 0. The number zero 0 cannot be used in place of the letter O on a personalized plate. **All verticals are keyed; Letter 'O' with letters and on personalized tags; number '0' with numbers. Letter 'O' is rounder than zero '0'. Example: LA-120COD (O with letters), LA-125841 (all-numeric), LA-MA3511 (OMIT slanted 'USMC'), LA-NA7440 (OMIT slanted 'NAVY'), LA-AR14772, LA-MH8521, LA-NG0000, LA-ARMY453. Always include stacked characters for Louisiana. Stacked characters must be keyed.

stacked_characters.position: ALWAYS INCLUDE stacked (MH, AR, NG, MA, NA) codes. OMIT slanted branch names (USMC, NAVY, ARMY). Include slanted if no stacked available.
stacked_characters.notes: ALWAYS include stacked characters including MH, AR, NG, MA, NA codes. OMIT slanted branch names (USMC, NAVY, ARMY). Include slanted text if no stacked available (e.g., LA-ARMY453)
